249
00:18:32.695 --> 00:18:33.946
It was like a tidal wave.

250
00:18:34.989 --> 00:18:37.074
I mean. they'd have you back
tomorrow if they could.

251
00:18:37.700 --> 00:18:39.285
We're very well set up
over there.

252
00:18:40.494 --> 00:18:41.495
Hmm.

253
00:18:42.163 --> 00:18:44.122
But. you know.
I think it's the next record

254
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:45.582
that's gonna
situate all of it.

255
00:18:47.001 --> 00:18:48.293
You know how it goes.

256
00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:49.920
Once you have
your first top ten.

257
00:18:49.921 --> 00:18:51.713
you know. they want three
for the next.

258
00:18:51.714 --> 00:18:53.131
You gotta feed the machine.

259
00:18:53.132 --> 00:18:54.633
That's not us. Jon.

260
00:18:55.551 --> 00:18:57.803
We've never been
about singles. but the album.

261
00:18:57.804 --> 00:18:59.179
Right? The whole story.

262
00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:00.181
No. I know.

263
00:19:00.765 --> 00:19:02.223
I mean. they're not thinking
about albums.

264
00:19:02.224 --> 00:19:03.851
They're just thinking
about momentum.

265
00:19:04.601 --> 00:19:05.852
Right.

266
00:19:05.853 --> 00:19:07.646
You know? The big picture.

267
00:19:10.983 --> 00:19:12.694
Hey. they're just excited.

268
00:19:13.778 --> 00:19:16.363
You know. they wanna make sure
we don't lose steam.

269
00:19:24.538 --> 00:19:25.748
It's hard coming home.

270
00:19:29.001 --> 00:19:30.795
Quiet can get a little loud.

271
00:19:32.714 --> 00:19:33.881
But that's. you know...

272
00:19:35.382 --> 00:19:37.676
Coming off the road has never
been easy for you.

273
00:19:40.137 --> 00:19:41.304
Yeah.

274
00:19:41.305 --> 00:19:42.724
You just need to give it
some time.

275
00:19:43.307 --> 00:19:44.433
It'll pass.

276
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:47.854
Yeah. Yeah.

277
00:19:55.527 --> 00:20:00.073
You know. I've been. um...
thinking about what you said.

278
00:20:00.074 --> 00:20:02.242
Next time we go in the studio.
you know.

279
00:20:02.243 --> 00:20:04.494
don't waste all the time
and money writing in there.

280
00:20:04.495 --> 00:20:06.162
We wanna come ready
with the material.

281
00:20:06.163 --> 00:20:07.497
That's smart.

282
00:20:07.498 --> 00:20:10.000
You finished <i>The River</i>
with only 20K in the bank.

283
00:20:10.001 --> 00:20:11.084
Right.

284
00:20:11.085 --> 00:20:12.377
You spent all your money
in the studio

285
00:20:12.378 --> 00:20:13.461
finishing the record.

286
00:20:13.462 --> 00:20:14.796
You don't need
to do that again.

287
00:20:14.797 --> 00:20:18.133
I read about these machines.
You know. they're new.

288
00:20:18.134 --> 00:20:20.594
You can multitrack at home.
you know. for cheap.

289
00:20:21.303 --> 00:20:23.013
They record on quarter-inch?

290
00:20:23.014 --> 00:20:24.140
No. cassettes.

291
00:20:24.807 --> 00:20:27.017
Cassettes? How many tracks?

292
00:20:27.018 --> 00:20:29.435
Four. You can get
basic arrangement down.

293
00:20:29.436 --> 00:20:32.563
You know. a little bit more
than guitar. vocal demo.

294
00:20:32.564 --> 00:20:33.731
They don't sound great.

295
00:20:33.732 --> 00:20:36.609
but. you know. it's not about
capturing sounds

296
00:20:36.610 --> 00:20:38.404
so much as ideas.

297
00:20:40.782 --> 00:20:41.990
Look into it.

298
00:20:41.991 --> 00:20:43.034
Oh. I am.

299
00:20:46.453 --> 00:20:48.873
Love you. Bruce!
"Hungry Heart"!

300
00:20:50.749 --> 00:20:51.834
See that?

301
00:20:52.543 --> 00:20:54.753
I'm telling you.
hit singles aren't so bad.

302
00:20:56.130 --> 00:20:57.380
Right?

303
00:20:57.381 --> 00:21:01.302
<i>...one. two. three. four</i>.

304
00:21:03.012 --> 00:21:06.932
<i>...of</i> Family Feud.
<i>Richard Dawson.</i>

305
00:21:08.017 --> 00:21:09.100
<i>This final note.</i>

306
00:21:09.101 --> 00:21:11.519
<i>Now. once you started
to get MTV.</i>

307
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:12.688
<i>I bet you thought
you had all--</i>

308
00:21:16.525 --> 00:21:19.402
<i>My girl Holly and I
decided to kill ourselves.</i>

309
00:21:19.403 --> 00:21:22.030
<i>The same way I did her daddy.
Big decision.</i>

310
00:21:22.031 --> 00:21:23.907
<i>Kit left a record
playing over and over</i>

311
00:21:23.908 --> 00:21:25.367
<i>for the district attorney
to find.</i>

312
00:21:25.952 --> 00:21:27.536
<i>He was gambling for time.</i>

313
00:21:28.079 --> 00:21:29.662
<i>But one thing though.</i>

314
00:21:29.663 --> 00:21:32.208
<i>He was provoking me
when I popped him.</i>

315
00:21:32.708 --> 00:21:35.502
<i>Well. that's
what it was like. Pop.</i>

316
00:23:01.880 --> 00:23:03.090
<i>Suppose I shot you.</i>

317
00:23:04.300 --> 00:23:05.301
<i>How'd that be?</i>

318
00:23:06.052 --> 00:23:07.053
<i>Huh?</i>

319
00:23:08.512 --> 00:23:10.055
<i>Wanna hear
what it sounds like?</i>

320
00:23:18.439 --> 00:23:24.320
<i>♪ He saw her standing
On her front lawn ♪</i>

321
00:23:26.488 --> 00:23:32.203
<i>♪ Twirling her baton ♪</i>

322
00:23:35.497 --> 00:23:40.126
<i>♪ Him and her went ♪</i>

323
00:23:40.127 --> 00:23:42.254
<i>♪ For a ride. sir ♪</i>

324
00:23:44.715 --> 00:23:50.428
<i>♪ Ten innocent people died ♪</i>

325
00:23:50.429 --> 00:23:52.974
- <i>Kit! Kit!
- Hey. where are you going?</i>

326
00:23:53.599 --> 00:23:54.558
<i>Daddy!</i>

327
00:24:01.023 --> 00:24:02.149
<i>Daddy?</i>

328
00:24:03.942 --> 00:24:05.443
<i>This is Holly.</i>

329
00:24:07.904 --> 00:24:09.656
<i>Are you gonna be okay?</i>

330
00:24:27.633 --> 00:24:29.342
I can't take it anymore.

331
00:24:29.343 --> 00:24:31.219
Day after day
it's the same thing.

332
00:24:31.220 --> 00:24:32.762
And I won't sit back
and watch you--

333
00:24:32.763 --> 00:24:33.929
You terrified him tonight!

334
00:24:33.930 --> 00:24:35.056
- No.
- Yes. you did!

335
00:24:35.057 --> 00:24:37.225
- You saw the look on his face.
- No.

336
00:24:37.226 --> 00:24:39.269
You come home. you're
a completely different person.

337
00:24:39.270 --> 00:24:41.187
- No. I'm not.
- You're a bully. Yes. you are!

338
00:24:41.188 --> 00:24:42.772
You're a bully!
You don't even realize it.

339
00:24:42.773 --> 00:24:43.814
Night after night.

340
00:24:43.815 --> 00:24:46.067
I have to send our 8-year-old
son into that bar

341
00:24:46.068 --> 00:24:47.568
to pull you out.

342
00:24:47.569 --> 00:24:49.112
Aren't you ashamed
of yourself?

343
00:24:49.113 --> 00:24:50.696
Do you even realize?
Look at yourself.

344
00:24:50.697 --> 00:24:52.907
You don't even realize
what a disgrace you are.

345
00:24:52.908 --> 00:24:55.410
Yeah. a disgrace!
I said. a disgrace!

346
00:25:15.764 --> 00:25:16.765
That's right.

347
00:25:18.725 --> 00:25:22.396
Don't ever let anybody
hurt your mother.

348
00:25:28.235 --> 00:25:30.154
- Are you okay?
- Mm-hmm.

349
00:26:17.493 --> 00:26:19.202
Coming!
I'll be right there!

350
00:26:19.203 --> 00:26:21.205
Will somebody get the door?

351
00:26:23.374 --> 00:26:28.044
Hi. Happy New Year. Um...

352
00:26:30.839 --> 00:26:33.216
- Does Faye live here?
- Who are you?

353
00:26:33.217 --> 00:26:34.509
I'm Bruce. Who are you?

354
00:26:34.510 --> 00:26:37.262
I'm Haley.
I just had a hot dog.

355
00:26:37.263 --> 00:26:39.054
I love hot dogs.
You have mustard or ketchup?

356
00:26:39.055 --> 00:26:40.140
Mustard.

357
00:26:40.141 --> 00:26:41.308
That's my favorite too.

358
00:26:42.476 --> 00:26:43.893
- Hi.
- Hi.

359
00:26:43.894 --> 00:26:46.354
We weren't sure you were
gonna show up. Were we. baby?

360
00:26:46.355 --> 00:26:47.813
I'm sorry I'm so late.

361
00:26:47.814 --> 00:26:49.857
I got caught up
with something.

362
00:26:49.858 --> 00:26:51.943
It's okay. We're used to men
not keeping their word.

363
00:26:53.737 --> 00:26:54.779
Haley. come on.

364
00:26:54.780 --> 00:26:55.905
I'm joking. I'm sorry.
Sort of.

365
00:26:55.906 --> 00:26:57.907
- Let's finally get you to bed.
- I love you. Goodbye.

366
00:26:57.908 --> 00:26:59.534
Good night.
Be good for Nana and Poppy.

367
00:26:59.535 --> 00:27:01.328
- When are you gonna be back?
- Don't wait up.

368
00:27:04.122 --> 00:27:05.456
- Hi.
- Hi.

369
00:27:05.457 --> 00:27:07.542
I'm just staying here
until I can get another job.

370
00:27:07.543 --> 00:27:08.877
and then I can get
my own place.

371
00:27:09.420 --> 00:27:11.086
- Okay.
- I'm really glad you came.

372
00:27:11.087 --> 00:27:13.005
Me too.

373
00:27:13.006 --> 00:27:14.633
- Let's go have some fun.
- Yeah.

374
00:27:15.592 --> 00:27:16.802
Where are we going?

375
00:27:17.303 --> 00:27:20.180
- Just go for a drive.
- Yeah?

376
00:28:16.987 --> 00:28:18.614
Hope we don't get
into trouble.

377
00:28:19.240 --> 00:28:21.242
We get in trouble.
I'm doing something wrong.

378
00:28:21.950 --> 00:28:24.536
In this town. I'm king.

379
00:28:30.417 --> 00:28:31.710
No way.

380
00:28:32.836 --> 00:28:34.338
- That's cool.
- Come on.

381
00:28:35.797 --> 00:28:37.466
- Are we getting on?
- Oh. yeah.

382
00:28:47.142 --> 00:28:48.809
Do you bring
all your dates here?

383
00:28:48.810 --> 00:28:50.145
Well. not at 2:00 a.m.

384
00:28:52.105 --> 00:28:53.481
Well. I don't care
what time it is.

385
00:28:53.482 --> 00:28:55.066
It's one of
my favorite places.

386
00:28:59.405 --> 00:29:00.656
You smile a lot.

387
00:29:02.824 --> 00:29:04.242
Is smiling illegal?

388
00:29:05.243 --> 00:29:06.453
Not in Asbury.

389
00:29:09.706 --> 00:29:11.500
What's Faye like to do
in her free time?

390
00:29:12.793 --> 00:29:14.627
Well. Faye doesn't have
free time.

391
00:29:14.628 --> 00:29:16.086
Faye has Haley.

392
00:29:16.087 --> 00:29:17.088
Right.

393
00:29:19.007 --> 00:29:20.884
But when she does.

394
00:29:21.927 --> 00:29:23.803
Faye plays chess.

395
00:29:23.804 --> 00:29:25.137
Chess?

396
00:29:25.138 --> 00:29:27.181
Yeah. what's wrong with that?

397
00:29:27.182 --> 00:29:28.684
There's nothing wrong
with that.

398
00:29:29.310 --> 00:29:30.727
It's cool as hell.

399
00:29:31.978 --> 00:29:33.439
I listen to a lot of music.

400
00:29:34.272 --> 00:29:35.899
Well.
who's in Faye's rotation?

401
00:29:38.485 --> 00:29:41.236
You know. Lou Reed.
Debbie Harry.

402
00:29:41.237 --> 00:29:42.947
Patti Smith. of course.

403
00:29:42.948 --> 00:29:44.450
- Sure.
- Um...

404
00:29:45.867 --> 00:29:47.452
This guy Bruce Springsteen.

405
00:29:47.453 --> 00:29:49.119
I don't know
if you've heard of him.

406
00:29:49.120 --> 00:29:50.456
- That guy?
- Yeah.

407
00:29:51.832 --> 00:29:52.958
You have good taste.

408
00:29:53.459 --> 00:29:55.043
- Oh. yeah?
- Hmm.

409
00:29:58.088 --> 00:29:59.506
Hey. that night we met...

410
00:30:00.215 --> 00:30:02.174
That your first time
at the Pony?

411
00:30:02.175 --> 00:30:03.468
I've been going to Pony since

412
00:30:03.469 --> 00:30:05.011
they've been letting me
into the Pony.

413
00:30:06.304 --> 00:30:07.262
And if I'm being honest.

414
00:30:07.263 --> 00:30:09.224
I don't think I've ever been
there when you haven't.

415
00:30:10.726 --> 00:30:11.767
If I'm being honest.

416
00:30:11.768 --> 00:30:13.395
I can't believe
I never noticed you.

417
00:30:16.773 --> 00:30:17.858
Happy New Year.

418
00:30:30.871 --> 00:30:32.789
I hope I'm not
making a mistake.

419
00:30:39.796 --> 00:30:41.882
I'm definitely
making a mistake.

420
00:30:47.513 --> 00:30:51.557
Susie Jenkins kept me busy
till about 11:58.

421
00:30:51.558 --> 00:30:54.561
that's when slick Billy
McCluster decided to swoop in.

422
00:30:55.061 --> 00:30:57.021
You know how he is.
that little asshole.

423
00:30:58.440 --> 00:31:00.775
Let's just say.
I still can't close.

424
00:31:00.776 --> 00:31:02.359
You gotta close. Mikey.

425
00:31:02.360 --> 00:31:03.487
Don't I know it.

426
00:31:04.195 --> 00:31:05.738
But not closing
allowed me to go

427
00:31:05.739 --> 00:31:07.032
to the record shop. see Pete.

428
00:31:07.866 --> 00:31:12.704
He suggested this
TEAC 144 Portastudio.

429
00:31:13.288 --> 00:31:15.247
He says that you can use it
as a multitrack.

430
00:31:15.248 --> 00:31:17.709
but do not expect
studio quality.

431
00:31:18.251 --> 00:31:19.919
Says you may not even want
people to hear it.

432
00:31:19.920 --> 00:31:22.547
That's okay. It's just me.
I'm not making a record.

433
00:31:22.548 --> 00:31:24.089
Just roughing on some ideas.

434
00:31:24.090 --> 00:31:25.508
You know. and the acoustics
are great in there.

435
00:31:25.509 --> 00:31:27.135
- Nice and dead.
- Oh.

436
00:31:27.886 --> 00:31:30.095
Sounds like
you got some songs.

437
00:31:30.096 --> 00:31:31.305
I don't know what I got.

438
00:31:31.306 --> 00:31:32.932
But if I got anything good.

439
00:31:32.933 --> 00:31:34.934
we'll recut it
in the studio with the band.

440
00:31:34.935 --> 00:31:36.185
Anything else you need?

441
00:31:36.186 --> 00:31:38.187
- A couple of mics.
- Shit.

442
00:31:38.188 --> 00:31:40.690
I already got the J-200
acoustic and harmonicas.

443
00:31:40.691 --> 00:31:43.400
- I could use a 12-string.
- You use a glockenspiel?

444
00:31:43.401 --> 00:31:45.277
Definitely the glock.

445
00:31:45.278 --> 00:31:46.404
Set it down.

446
00:31:49.533 --> 00:31:51.117
Aren't you gonna wanna.
you know...

447
00:31:51.827 --> 00:31:52.911
Well. Mikey...

448
00:31:53.537 --> 00:31:57.457
Oh. I meant sleep. But hey.
I'm not judging.

449
00:31:57.458 --> 00:31:59.167
I think you just did.

450
00:32:00.168 --> 00:32:01.877
Nice carpet. Boss.

451
00:32:01.878 --> 00:32:05.173
Some candles or bourbon
might take the sting off.

452
00:32:07.175 --> 00:32:09.384
God. man. At least let me hang
a poster or something.

453
00:32:09.385 --> 00:32:11.929
Maybe over this.
This thing's creeping me out.

454
00:32:11.930 --> 00:32:13.639
I'm just singing
in the shower.

455
00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:14.683
"Singing in the shower."

456
00:32:15.183 --> 00:32:17.309
- You know I'm not a mixer.
- Yeah. course I know.

457
00:32:17.310 --> 00:32:19.771
I don't know shit about
recording or whatever.

458
00:32:20.355 --> 00:32:21.857
I'm not making
a record. Mikey.

459
00:32:22.608 --> 00:32:24.942
I don't want an engineer or
producer judging this stuff.

460
00:32:24.943 --> 00:32:29.321
I just... want it to feel like
I'm in the room by myself.

461
00:32:29.322 --> 00:32:30.448
Then you've found your man.

462
00:32:39.040 --> 00:32:44.630
<i>♪ Now. the jury
Brought in a guilty verdict ♪</i>

463
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:51.928
<i>♪ And the judge
He sentenced me to death ♪</i>

464
00:32:53.597 --> 00:32:57.683
<i>♪ Midnight
In a prison storeroom... ♪</i>

465
00:32:57.684 --> 00:32:58.685
Hey!

466
00:33:01.271 --> 00:33:02.354
Jump in.

467
00:33:02.355 --> 00:33:03.607
But what about school?

468
00:33:04.190 --> 00:33:05.691
No school today.

469
00:33:05.692 --> 00:33:06.777
Really?

470
00:33:07.944 --> 00:33:09.279
Just you and me.

471
00:33:20.582 --> 00:33:21.917
<i>Speak.</i>

472
00:33:22.876 --> 00:33:24.126
<i>Speak or I'll cut your throat</i>

473
00:33:24.127 --> 00:33:25.795
<i>and leave you to drip
like a hog</i>

474
00:33:25.796 --> 00:33:26.880
<i>hung up in butchering time.</i>

475
00:33:27.463 --> 00:33:30.592
<i>Pearl. shut up!
Pearl. you swore!</i>

476
00:33:31.718 --> 00:33:33.386
<i>You could
save him. little bird.</i>

477
00:33:34.262 --> 00:33:36.597
<i>Inside my doll!
Inside my doll!</i>

478
00:33:36.598 --> 00:33:38.015
<i>The doll!</i>

479
00:33:38.016 --> 00:33:39.517
<i>Why. sure!</i>

480
00:33:40.936 --> 00:33:43.438
<i>The last place
anybody'd think to look.</i>

481
00:33:52.155 --> 00:33:57.661
<i>♪ They declared me
Unfit to live ♪</i>

482
00:33:58.494 --> 00:34:04.292
<i>♪ Said into that great void
My soul'd be hurled ♪</i>

483
00:34:06.127 --> 00:34:12.008
<i>♪ They want to know
Why I did what I did ♪</i>

484
00:34:12.759 --> 00:34:16.929
<i>♪ Sir. I guess
There's just a meanness ♪</i>

485
00:34:16.930 --> 00:34:19.182
<i>♪ In this world ♪</i>

486
00:34:52.298 --> 00:34:53.508
I think we got that.

487
00:34:54.509 --> 00:34:57.012
Oh. yeah. we got that one.

488
00:34:59.973 --> 00:35:01.725
So this song got a name?

489
00:35:03.769 --> 00:35:05.520
I was gonna call it
"Starkweather."

490
00:35:08.857 --> 00:35:10.483
But now I'm thinking
"Nebraska."

491
00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:33.524
Imagine that.

492
00:36:34.025 --> 00:36:36.236
Must be a small fortune
for that sucker.

493
00:36:39.655 --> 00:36:41.031
Live in something like that

494
00:36:41.032 --> 00:36:43.492
and all your problems
will disappear.

495
00:36:46.496 --> 00:36:49.374
All right. kids. Go run about.

496
00:36:56.214 --> 00:36:58.799
Look at that!

497
00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:00.675
<i>♪ There's a place ♪</i>

498
00:37:00.676 --> 00:37:05.973
<i>♪ Out on the edge
Of town. sir... ♪</i>

499
00:37:05.974 --> 00:37:07.975
Wait for me. Bruce!

500
00:37:07.976 --> 00:37:09.310
You're going too fast!

501
00:37:09.895 --> 00:37:11.312
Wait up!

502
00:37:13.439 --> 00:37:14.524
Yeah!

503
00:37:15.316 --> 00:37:16.734
Let's go!

504
00:37:17.778 --> 00:37:19.195
Whoo!

505
00:37:20.446 --> 00:37:21.948
Bruce!

506
00:37:23.784 --> 00:37:26.160
Yeah! Wait up!

507
00:37:29.790 --> 00:37:31.874
Wait up!

508
00:37:31.875 --> 00:37:33.542
<i>♪ In the day ♪</i>

509
00:37:33.543 --> 00:37:38.089
<i>♪ You can see
The children playing ♪</i>

510
00:37:38.673 --> 00:37:41.383
<i>♪ On the road that leads ♪</i>

511
00:37:41.384 --> 00:37:44.679
<i>♪ To those gates
Of hardened steel ♪</i>

512
00:37:47.473 --> 00:37:54.064
<i>♪ Steel gates that
Completely surround. sir ♪</i>

513
00:37:56.066 --> 00:38:02.280
<i>♪ The mansion on the hill ♪</i>

514
00:38:08.161 --> 00:38:09.244
I'm riding it.

515
00:38:09.245 --> 00:38:10.454
Do you remember
what noise a horse makes?

516
00:38:10.455 --> 00:38:11.371
Yep.

517
00:38:11.372 --> 00:38:12.372
Can you do it?

518
00:38:12.373 --> 00:38:13.499
That's it.

519
00:38:14.835 --> 00:38:15.750
Uh!

520
00:38:15.751 --> 00:38:17.669
You really didn't have
to do that.

521
00:38:17.670 --> 00:38:19.422
Hope she can have
some fun with it.

522
00:38:20.256 --> 00:38:22.175
Oh. yeah.
She's gonna have fun with it.

523
00:38:23.509 --> 00:38:24.928
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

524
00:38:26.596 --> 00:38:28.263
- Okay. I'm gonna get our stuff.
- Okay.

525
00:38:28.264 --> 00:38:30.057
- Wanna hang out with Bruce?
- Sure.

526
00:38:30.058 --> 00:38:32.392
- All right. let's do it.
- I'm gonna take this upstairs.

527
00:38:32.393 --> 00:38:34.228
- You want it in your room?
- Uh. sure.

528
00:38:34.229 --> 00:38:35.604
All right.
You wanna sit in the front

529
00:38:35.605 --> 00:38:36.646
or you wanna go in the back?

530
00:38:36.647 --> 00:38:37.772
- What do you think?
- The front!

531
00:38:37.773 --> 00:38:38.858
- The front?
- Yes!

532
00:38:38.859 --> 00:38:39.942
All right. you got it.

533
00:38:39.943 --> 00:38:41.861
Is that
that guitar player fella?

534
00:38:41.862 --> 00:38:43.696
Yes. Daddy.
That's Bruce Springsteen.

535
00:38:44.197 --> 00:38:46.741
Careful. huh?
Your Uncle Dave played guitar.

536
00:38:47.242 --> 00:38:48.742
Right. well.
Uncle Dave didn't sing.

537
00:38:48.743 --> 00:38:49.994
At least not like Bruce.

538
00:38:49.995 --> 00:38:52.454
Yeah. but
I don't want it right now.

539
00:38:52.455 --> 00:38:53.456
Okay.

540
00:38:54.332 --> 00:38:55.458
What did we decide?

541
00:38:56.209 --> 00:38:57.292
Dancing.

542
00:38:57.293 --> 00:38:58.919
- Dancing.
- That's dancing.

543
00:38:58.920 --> 00:39:02.173
- One. two. three!
- Three!

544
00:39:03.174 --> 00:39:04.216
Whoo!

545
00:39:04.217 --> 00:39:05.509
Wow!

546
00:39:05.510 --> 00:39:06.676
She is too fast.

547
00:39:06.677 --> 00:39:08.012
- She is too fast.
- She's catching up.

548
00:39:08.013 --> 00:39:09.263
Baby. you won!

549
00:39:09.264 --> 00:39:11.098
- Haley.
- Congratulations.

550
00:39:11.099 --> 00:39:12.225
What's that?

551
00:39:13.977 --> 00:39:15.269
See right there.

552
00:39:36.541 --> 00:39:37.666
Press the buttons.

553
00:39:37.667 --> 00:39:39.168
Just keep pressing them. huh?

554
00:39:39.169 --> 00:39:41.336
Yeah. never not be pressing
those buttons.

555
00:39:41.337 --> 00:39:45.465
Go Bruce. Go Bruce. Go Bruce.

556
00:39:45.466 --> 00:39:47.342
- Press that one.
- Press that one? No. no.

557
00:39:47.343 --> 00:39:49.844
- Higher up. Just a little bit.
- So we can go over the green.

558
00:39:49.845 --> 00:39:51.722
But don't go all the way
to the top. remember?

559
00:39:58.771 --> 00:40:00.773
<i>♪ I'm on fire ♪</i>

560
00:40:23.046 --> 00:40:24.629
Very serious.

561
00:40:24.630 --> 00:40:25.881
Hey!

562
00:40:27.175 --> 00:40:29.343
- Mommy got it. huh?
- Yay!

563
00:40:29.344 --> 00:40:31.554
There you go. Go ahead. Yes.

564
00:41:05.588 --> 00:41:07.756
She looks like an angel.

565
00:41:07.757 --> 00:41:09.091
She's out cold.

566
00:41:09.092 --> 00:41:11.135
She's been running around
all day.

567
00:41:11.136 --> 00:41:13.803
I can take her to the office.
It's quiet back there.

568
00:41:13.804 --> 00:41:15.555
Oh. no. no. It's fine.
Thank you. though.

569
00:41:15.556 --> 00:41:16.640
All right.

570
00:41:16.641 --> 00:41:20.186
Well. let me know
if you need anything.

571
00:41:20.770 --> 00:41:21.771
I will.

572
00:41:25.358 --> 00:41:26.942
That's Viv. She's my manager.

573
00:41:27.693 --> 00:41:29.029
She's the sweetest.

574
00:41:29.862 --> 00:41:31.281
So how long you worked here?

575
00:41:33.408 --> 00:41:35.160
- It's a little over a year.
- Hmm.

576
00:41:36.161 --> 00:41:38.996
I mean. it's a paycheck.
but they make me feel at home.

577
00:41:39.705 --> 00:41:40.956
I can tell.

578
00:41:45.545 --> 00:41:47.422
We had a really nice time.

579
00:41:49.174 --> 00:41:50.840
She really needed it.

580
00:41:50.841 --> 00:41:52.468
And honestly. so did I.

581
00:41:54.262 --> 00:41:56.097
You heard
from her father lately?

582
00:41:58.974 --> 00:42:00.101
Hardly ever.

583
00:42:02.687 --> 00:42:05.190
Turns out
we weren't his first rodeo.

584
00:42:07.650 --> 00:42:08.733
I'm sorry.

585
00:42:08.734 --> 00:42:10.110
It's okay.

586
00:42:10.111 --> 00:42:12.279
'cause I no longer have to
worry about what I should eat

587
00:42:12.280 --> 00:42:13.530
or what I should wear

588
00:42:13.531 --> 00:42:16.659
or whether my neck is long
enough for hoop earrings.

589
00:42:17.618 --> 00:42:18.953
It's a hard thing...

590
00:42:21.956 --> 00:42:24.542
realizing people aren't
who you want them to be.

591
00:42:27.587 --> 00:42:28.963
Hmm.

592
00:42:34.177 --> 00:42:36.137
I would say I'm a natural.
Wouldn't you?

593
00:42:37.054 --> 00:42:38.513
Yeah.
definitely a natural.

594
00:42:38.514 --> 00:42:40.266
Yeah.

595
00:42:44.187 --> 00:42:46.271
I don't know. I think
I found my true calling.

596
00:42:48.816 --> 00:42:50.651
Yeah. I think
you just might have.

597
00:44:15.695 --> 00:44:17.780
I've been thinking
about giving you this.

598
00:44:20.032 --> 00:44:21.116
What's that?

599
00:44:23.077 --> 00:44:24.662
It's my Saint Christopher.

600
00:44:30.460 --> 00:44:31.794
It's kept me safe.

601
00:44:38.175 --> 00:44:39.302
It's beautiful.

602
00:44:42.179 --> 00:44:44.307
Trust that it will protect you

603
00:44:45.266 --> 00:44:47.184
and guide you
where you're meant to go.

604
00:44:50.480 --> 00:44:51.647
Thank you.

605
00:44:55.235 --> 00:44:57.402
- I got a call from Jann.
- Mmm.

606
00:44:57.403 --> 00:44:58.904
And he wants
to do a feature on you.

607
00:44:59.697 --> 00:45:00.822
which I think could be great.

608
00:45:00.823 --> 00:45:01.906
Right.

609
00:45:01.907 --> 00:45:03.867
And then <i>The Tonight Show</i>.

610
00:45:03.868 --> 00:45:06.328
you know. Carson's team.
they reached out again.

611
00:45:06.329 --> 00:45:08.830
So they're really pushing hard
for you to come on the show.

612
00:45:08.831 --> 00:45:10.291
I told 'em
we'd think about it.

613
00:45:11.125 --> 00:45:12.543
It's all piling up. huh?

614
00:45:13.628 --> 00:45:15.546
You're not a bar band
musician anymore.

615
00:45:16.046 --> 00:45:17.213
It's the big time.

616
00:45:17.214 --> 00:45:18.882
- Big time.
- Big pile.

617
00:45:19.842 --> 00:45:21.175
Big pile.

618
00:45:21.176 --> 00:45:22.428
On that subject...

619
00:45:23.929 --> 00:45:25.889
- You know Paul Schrader?
- The writer?

620
00:45:25.890 --> 00:45:28.643
He wrote <i>Taxi Driver</i>.
Great movie.

621
00:45:30.019 --> 00:45:31.185
He sent this over.

622
00:45:31.186 --> 00:45:32.355
Thought you'd might like it.

623
00:45:32.980 --> 00:45:34.148
"Born in the U.S.A."

624
00:45:35.316 --> 00:45:36.776
He wants me
to write a song for it?

625
00:45:37.277 --> 00:45:40.028
Write a song and star in it.
You know. act in it.

626
00:45:40.029 --> 00:45:41.321
Star in it?

627
00:45:41.322 --> 00:45:43.156
Yeah. You and De Niro.

628
00:45:44.367 --> 00:45:45.450
No shit.

629
00:45:45.451 --> 00:45:47.161
- That's what he says.
- Wow.

630
00:45:47.828 --> 00:45:48.912
Okay.

631
00:45:48.913 --> 00:45:50.914
Yeah. I'll give it a read.
I'll give it a read.

632
00:45:50.915 --> 00:45:52.416
- Great.
- Okay. Jon.

633
00:45:52.417 --> 00:45:54.000
- Thanks for coming in.
- Good to see you.

634
00:45:54.001 --> 00:45:56.085
Hang on a second.
I got one more thing.

635
00:45:56.086 --> 00:45:58.505
We're scheduled to record
"Cover Me"...

636
00:45:58.506 --> 00:45:59.423
Ah.

637
00:45:59.424 --> 00:46:02.759
...for Donna Summer
around January 25th.

638
00:46:02.760 --> 00:46:04.218
- Okay.
- Do you feel good about that?

639
00:46:04.219 --> 00:46:05.429
'Cause Geffen keeps calling

640
00:46:05.430 --> 00:46:06.638
and I assured him
it's happening.

641
00:46:06.639 --> 00:46:07.722
Yeah. yeah. no.

642
00:46:07.723 --> 00:46:09.891
Honestly. I haven't given it
too much thought.

643
00:46:09.892 --> 00:46:11.601
I think I got something
to work from.

644
00:46:11.602 --> 00:46:13.978
but I'm on that other wave
right now. you know?

645
00:46:13.979 --> 00:46:16.022
Those other songs.
they're feeling good. So...

646
00:46:16.023 --> 00:46:17.441
Great.
Well. you ride that wave.

647
00:46:17.442 --> 00:46:18.942
But Dave is telling Quincy

648
00:46:18.943 --> 00:46:20.193
they'll have something
by February.

649
00:46:20.194 --> 00:46:22.488
so we got a little time.
Just not a lot.

650
00:46:24.073 --> 00:46:25.365
- Okay.
- Hey.

651
00:46:25.366 --> 00:46:28.786
Hey. if this is all too much.
let's just pull back.

652
00:46:29.286 --> 00:46:30.371
You say the word.

653
00:46:31.331 --> 00:46:32.622
Oh. no. I'm okay.

654
00:46:32.623 --> 00:46:36.461
Just trying to find something
real in all the noise.

655
00:46:37.753 --> 00:46:39.087
You always do. Okay?

656
00:46:39.088 --> 00:46:41.840
But don't push it.
We'll let it find you.

657
00:46:41.841 --> 00:46:43.299
Okay.

658
00:46:43.300 --> 00:46:45.635
You find something real.
I'll deal with the noise.

659
00:46:45.636 --> 00:46:48.930
- You deal with the noise.
- It's my job.

660
00:46:48.931 --> 00:46:50.057
Thanks. Jon.

661
00:47:01.235 --> 00:47:03.945
<i>♪ My little sister's
In the front seat ♪</i>

662
00:47:03.946 --> 00:47:05.948
<i>♪ With an ice cream cone... ♪</i>

663
00:47:07.492 --> 00:47:09.534
This little bastard's wonky.

664
00:47:09.535 --> 00:47:10.827
Yeah.

665
00:47:10.828 --> 00:47:12.286
I tested it and it mixed down.

666
00:47:12.287 --> 00:47:14.581
but I don't know
about the sound quality.

667
00:47:14.582 --> 00:47:15.707
What do you think?

668
00:47:15.708 --> 00:47:17.084
Eh. it's not a surprise.

669
00:47:17.585 --> 00:47:19.919
You know. Gary and I
took it out boating.

670
00:47:19.920 --> 00:47:22.172
hit some rough waters
and a wave got it.

671
00:47:22.673 --> 00:47:24.466
And it was dead
for a couple of months.

672
00:47:24.467 --> 00:47:26.134
Then it dried out.

673
00:47:26.135 --> 00:47:28.219
came back to life.
scared the hell out of me.

674
00:47:29.138 --> 00:47:30.472
I believe it.

675
00:47:30.473 --> 00:47:33.475
That's some
weird <i>Exorcist</i> shit.

676
00:47:33.476 --> 00:47:34.934
Its head might start spinning.

677
00:47:34.935 --> 00:47:36.562
Listen. Mikey. I. uh...

678
00:47:37.062 --> 00:47:39.481
I want us to run everything
through this Echoplex.

679
00:47:39.482 --> 00:47:41.775
All right? On all the tracks
we're mixing.

680
00:47:41.776 --> 00:47:44.111
You know. just like
Elvis's early Sun records.

681
00:47:44.904 --> 00:47:46.155
Elvis. yeah.

682
00:47:47.072 --> 00:47:48.740
You're sure though. Boss?

683
00:47:48.741 --> 00:47:50.742
I know that once you put
the echo on it.

684
00:47:50.743 --> 00:47:52.368
you can't undo it.

685
00:47:52.369 --> 00:47:53.579
Yeah. I'm sure. Mikey.

686
00:47:55.289 --> 00:47:59.000
<i>♪ Now. mister
The day the lottery I win ♪</i>

687
00:47:59.001 --> 00:48:04.298
<i>♪ I ain't ever gonna ride
In no used car again ♪</i>

688
00:48:06.551 --> 00:48:10.261
<i>♪ Now the neighbors come
From near and far... ♪</i>

689
00:48:10.262 --> 00:48:11.722
Are you hearing that. Boss?

690
00:48:12.682 --> 00:48:14.517
The tape's speed is off.

691
00:48:15.142 --> 00:48:17.978
It's playing back slower.

692
00:48:19.313 --> 00:48:20.229
I don't know.

693
00:48:20.230 --> 00:48:21.732
Whatever's off
sounds just right to me.

694
00:48:27.196 --> 00:48:28.573
Man. I really love it.

695
00:48:30.616 --> 00:48:33.410
<i>♪ Listen
To my last prayer... ♪</i>

696
00:48:33.994 --> 00:48:35.412
Well. it's different.

697
00:48:36.497 --> 00:48:37.873
Definitely not "Hungry Heart."

698
00:48:38.373 --> 00:48:41.126
<i>♪ Deliver me from nowhere ♪</i>

699
00:48:45.965 --> 00:48:47.257
<i>♪ Whoo! ♪</i>

700
00:48:48.425 --> 00:48:50.760
<i>♪ Whoo! ♪</i>

701
00:48:50.761 --> 00:48:53.138
<i>♪ Seemed kinda funny. sir
To me ♪</i>

702
00:48:54.306 --> 00:48:57.100
<i>♪ Still at the end
Of every hard day ♪</i>

703
00:48:57.101 --> 00:49:00.312
<i>♪ People find
Some reason to believe ♪</i>

704
00:49:21.751 --> 00:49:22.752
Man.

705
00:49:24.211 --> 00:49:25.921
I love the short echo.

706
00:49:27.339 --> 00:49:28.715
I don't know
what Jon's gonna think.

707
00:49:28.716 --> 00:49:32.512
but there's something
I can't quite grasp.

708
00:49:35.556 --> 00:49:37.808
I think it's the distance
that we're hearing.

709
00:49:39.519 --> 00:49:42.146
You know. it's like it's from
the past or something.

710
00:49:45.190 --> 00:49:46.609
So how's it going with Faye?

711
00:49:47.693 --> 00:49:49.027
It's going good. I guess.

712
00:49:49.028 --> 00:49:50.404
But you know me...

713
00:49:51.363 --> 00:49:53.197
I'm not gonna
make it easy on her.

714
00:49:53.198 --> 00:49:56.159
Come on. Don't tell me
she's another drive-by?

715
00:49:56.160 --> 00:49:57.661
Ah. she's a great gal.

716
00:49:57.662 --> 00:50:00.329
but I can feel
I'm getting in my own way.

717
00:50:00.330 --> 00:50:02.666
Being with you
can be painful business.

718
00:50:02.667 --> 00:50:04.543
Thanks for the morale boost.

719
00:50:04.544 --> 00:50:06.336
Are you saying I can't change?

720
00:50:07.296 --> 00:50:08.297
No.

721
00:50:08.839 --> 00:50:11.007
I'm just saying
I'd like to see it.

722
00:50:11.008 --> 00:50:12.425
I don't know. Matty.

723
00:50:12.426 --> 00:50:13.635
When I'm deep in my work.

724
00:50:13.636 --> 00:50:15.888
I'm just not much good
for anything else.

725
00:50:16.556 --> 00:50:17.556
At least we're not breaking up

726
00:50:17.557 --> 00:50:19.558
on a weekly basis
like you and Teresa.

727
00:50:19.559 --> 00:50:20.600
That's my future wife

728
00:50:20.601 --> 00:50:21.851
you're talking about
right there.

729
00:50:21.852 --> 00:50:23.519
You watch your mouth.

730
00:50:23.520 --> 00:50:25.647
Seriously.
if she's worth it to you.

731
00:50:25.648 --> 00:50:26.690
make the effort.

732
00:50:26.691 --> 00:50:27.692
Don't half-ass it.

733
00:50:28.358 --> 00:50:30.194
So when is this thing
gonna be done?

734
00:50:31.278 --> 00:50:32.446
I don't know.

735
00:50:33.530 --> 00:50:35.865
How about your wedding day?

736
00:50:35.866 --> 00:50:37.784
Hey. What do you think
you're doing?

737
00:50:37.785 --> 00:50:39.160
Two feet away. please.
Come on.

738
00:50:39.161 --> 00:50:40.745
- This is a work of art here.
- All right.

739
00:50:40.746 --> 00:50:41.663
All right?

740
00:50:41.664 --> 00:50:44.498
Do I come into your studio
and pick up your guitar?

741
00:50:44.499 --> 00:50:45.541
Come on.

742
00:50:45.542 --> 00:50:48.086
That's Ahmet.
That's... That's his genius.

743
00:50:48.087 --> 00:50:51.380
You know.
he shaped the... uh...

744
00:50:51.381 --> 00:50:53.925
What's it... Phil Collins.
"In the Air Tonight."

745
00:50:53.926 --> 00:50:55.551
You know. that's... that's...

746
00:50:55.552 --> 00:50:57.136
That's... that's why...

747
00:50:57.137 --> 00:50:58.221
Come on in.

748
00:50:58.222 --> 00:50:59.932
Let me... You know.
let me call you back.

749
00:51:02.351 --> 00:51:03.352
Great.

750
00:51:04.937 --> 00:51:06.355
- Hey. Jon.
- How we doing?

751
00:51:07.147 --> 00:51:08.816
Didn't trust
the delivery service.

752
00:51:13.779 --> 00:51:14.905
Where's the case?

753
00:51:17.407 --> 00:51:19.159
- For the tape?
- For the tape.

754
00:51:19.869 --> 00:51:22.496
No case. but he did
give me this letter.

755
00:51:26.291 --> 00:51:27.584
