trying to make it better.

1103
01:15:12.925 --> 01:15:14.592
We're just making it worse.

1104
01:15:14.593 --> 01:15:17.429
<i>♪ At least
For a little while. sir... ♪</i>

1105
01:15:17.430 --> 01:15:18.930
I don't wanna
make it better. Jon.

1106
01:15:18.931 --> 01:15:23.017
<i>♪ Me and her
We had us some fun ♪</i>

1107
01:15:23.018 --> 01:15:24.644
I just...
I just wanna get back to

1108
01:15:24.645 --> 01:15:26.688
what happened in the bedroom.

1109
01:15:26.689 --> 01:15:28.273
That's it.

1110
01:15:28.274 --> 01:15:30.942
<i>♪ ...brought
In a guilty verdict ♪</i>

1111
01:15:32.528 --> 01:15:34.113
Gonna put the others
on the shelf.

1112
01:15:35.448 --> 01:15:36.907
"Born in the U.S.A."

1113
01:15:37.408 --> 01:15:39.409
"I'm On Fire." "Glory Days."

1114
01:15:39.410 --> 01:15:41.536
This is what
we're putting out. okay?

1115
01:15:41.537 --> 01:15:43.663
These songs. just as they are.

1116
01:15:43.664 --> 01:15:45.499
<i>♪ ...prison storeroom ♪</i>

1117
01:15:46.834 --> 01:15:49.086
<i>♪ With leather straps
Across... ♪</i>

1118
01:15:49.087 --> 01:15:50.670
Chuck. you just...

1119
01:15:50.671 --> 01:15:53.298
master directly off the tape.
Please.

1120
01:15:53.299 --> 01:15:54.592
Directly off the tape.

1121
01:15:57.386 --> 01:15:59.722
Man.
I love "Born in the U.S.A."

1122
01:16:03.559 --> 01:16:04.892
<i>This is nuts. Jon</i>.

1123
01:16:04.893 --> 01:16:06.436
<i>You know it. I know it.</i>

1124
01:16:06.437 --> 01:16:09.189
<i>And somewhere deep inside.
Bruce knows it.</i>

1125
01:16:09.190 --> 01:16:10.315
- All right.
<i>- That's what he's doing.</i>

1126
01:16:10.316 --> 01:16:13.110
I'm not going there. Jimmy.
But. you know. I...

1127
01:16:13.111 --> 01:16:15.695
Yeah. I don't understand
putting this stuff aside.

1128
01:16:15.696 --> 01:16:17.155
Bruce knows how good it is.

1129
01:16:17.156 --> 01:16:18.698
And as his former engineer.

1130
01:16:18.699 --> 01:16:20.617
you understand how good it is.
You know what it is.

1131
01:16:20.618 --> 01:16:22.410
<i>"Born in the U.S.A."
is exactly</i>

1132
01:16:22.411 --> 01:16:23.703
<i>what he needs right now.</i>

1133
01:16:23.704 --> 01:16:26.706
<i>The only shelf
he should put this on</i>

1134
01:16:26.707 --> 01:16:28.208
<i>is a shelf in a record store.</i>

1135
01:16:28.209 --> 01:16:29.709
<i>- not in his recording studio.</i>
- I told him.

1136
01:16:29.710 --> 01:16:30.627
- He's not--
<i>- That's it.</i>

1137
01:16:30.628 --> 01:16:31.544
Jimmy. listen to me.

1138
01:16:31.545 --> 01:16:33.671
Right now. he's doing
this other stuff. Okay?

1139
01:16:33.672 --> 01:16:35.006
<i>What other stuff?</i>

1140
01:16:35.007 --> 01:16:37.592
Well. you know.
the acoustic stuff.

1141
01:16:37.593 --> 01:16:39.511
The songs
he recorded in his bedroom.

1142
01:16:39.512 --> 01:16:40.845
<i>The folk album?</i>

1143
01:16:40.846 --> 01:16:43.390
<i>He's gonna put out
a fucking folk album?</i>

1144
01:16:43.391 --> 01:16:44.641
Jimmy. Jesus.

1145
01:16:44.642 --> 01:16:46.018
<i>That's insane.</i>

1146
01:16:46.852 --> 01:16:48.396
I think he's afraid...

1147
01:16:50.481 --> 01:16:51.732
of what's coming.

1148
01:16:53.151 --> 01:16:54.610
You know.
how big it could get.

1149
01:16:56.737 --> 01:17:00.658
You know. success.
it's complicated for Bruce.

1150
01:17:02.576 --> 01:17:03.535
And these...

1151
01:17:03.536 --> 01:17:05.954
these songs are about
someone who is guilty.

1152
01:17:07.956 --> 01:17:11.459
And he feels guilty
