1154
01:17:13.796 --> 01:17:15.380
The world he knows.

1155
01:17:15.381 --> 01:17:16.714
Losing that connection.

1156
01:17:16.715 --> 01:17:19.342
- Mm-hmm.
- It's eating him alive.

1157
01:17:19.343 --> 01:17:20.636
You know. I can't...

1158
01:17:24.515 --> 01:17:26.140
I can't reach him.

1159
01:17:26.141 --> 01:17:28.435
<i>♪ Well. they blew up
The chicken man ♪</i>

1160
01:17:28.436 --> 01:17:30.478
<i>♪ In Philly last night ♪</i>

1161
01:17:30.479 --> 01:17:33.899
<i>♪ Now they blew up
His house too ♪</i>

1162
01:17:34.567 --> 01:17:37.236
<i>♪ Down on the boardwalk
They're getting ready... ♪</i>

1163
01:17:38.779 --> 01:17:39.947
I know.

1164
01:17:40.489 --> 01:17:43.326
The distortion is still there.
I... I can't get rid of it.

1165
01:17:46.078 --> 01:17:47.370
Look.

1166
01:17:47.371 --> 01:17:48.996
Bruce. you cut this
on equipment

1167
01:17:48.997 --> 01:17:51.958
that doesn't exactly meet
our usual standards.

1168
01:17:51.959 --> 01:17:53.419
I can keep trying.

1169
01:17:54.127 --> 01:17:56.879
but this is a very
unconventional situation.

1170
01:17:56.880 --> 01:17:58.924
I don't care how
unconventional it is. Chuck.

1171
01:17:59.467 --> 01:18:02.219
But it...
it wasn't recorded properly.

1172
01:18:02.220 --> 01:18:05.054
and the distortion
is a result of that--

1173
01:18:05.055 --> 01:18:06.474
- I...
- Hey. hey. hey.

1174
01:18:08.226 --> 01:18:10.228
That's it. Okay?

1175
01:18:12.438 --> 01:18:13.605
Everybody...

1176
01:18:13.606 --> 01:18:15.565
We're done
for the night. guys.

1177
01:18:15.566 --> 01:18:16.567
Everybody out.

1178
01:18:29.747 --> 01:18:31.290
<i>What are we dealing with here?</i>

1179
01:18:32.958 --> 01:18:34.959
You know. they do want hits

1180
01:18:34.960 --> 01:18:36.712
and not a... not a breakdown.

1181
01:18:38.464 --> 01:18:40.466
I mean. is this about
the record? Or is this...

1182
01:18:42.050 --> 01:18:44.345
Because I'm... I'm out
of my depth on this one.

1183
01:18:46.930 --> 01:18:49.015
Yeah. well. something
just doesn't feel right.

1184
01:18:49.016 --> 01:18:50.224
You know?

1185
01:18:50.225 --> 01:18:52.310
- Right.
- But those songs.

1186
01:18:52.311 --> 01:18:55.230
they're the only thing
making sense to me right now.

1187
01:18:58.651 --> 01:19:00.528
It's the only thing
I can still believe in.

1188
01:19:03.864 --> 01:19:05.198
Then we'll get it.

1189
01:19:07.117 --> 01:19:08.369
Whatever it takes.

1190
01:19:09.912 --> 01:19:10.996
Okay?

1191
01:19:12.039 --> 01:19:13.623
We'll get it.

1192
01:19:13.624 --> 01:19:16.418
I'll have to adjust
the depth and the distance

1193
01:19:16.419 --> 01:19:19.422
between the grooves
by hand. the old way.

1194
01:19:20.298 --> 01:19:22.299
and cut it
at an incredibly low level.

1195
01:19:22.300 --> 01:19:24.760
so the needle doesn't dig
too deeply into the vinyl.

1196
01:19:26.470 --> 01:19:29.389
But people have knobs. right?

1197
01:19:29.390 --> 01:19:31.641
They can
turn it up themselves.

1198
01:19:31.642 --> 01:19:33.518
Well. I'd rather
they didn't have to. Dennis.

1199
01:19:33.519 --> 01:19:35.312
but we have no choice.

1200
01:19:35.313 --> 01:19:38.566
And. when I say that.
we have no choice.

1201
01:19:39.317 --> 01:19:41.944
Look. as long as Bruce knows
I only have old gear.

1202
01:19:42.820 --> 01:19:44.779
Let's give it a shot.

1203
01:19:44.780 --> 01:19:45.989
Yeah. great.

1204
01:19:46.865 --> 01:19:48.867
Where's the case for this?

1205
01:19:49.535 --> 01:19:51.160
I have no idea.

1206
01:20:38.959 --> 01:20:40.210
There you go.

1207
01:20:40.919 --> 01:20:42.380
You want me to top that?

1208
01:20:44.757 --> 01:20:45.882
- Thank you. sweetheart.
- Enjoy.

1209
01:20:45.883 --> 01:20:46.966
Anybody else?

1210
