1223
01:21:49.780 --> 01:21:51.448
<i>Hey. it's me.</i>

1224
01:21:51.449 --> 01:21:52.616
<i>Leave me a message.</i>

1225
01:21:54.827 --> 01:21:56.119
<i>If you're there. pick up.</i>

1226
01:21:57.788 --> 01:22:00.372
<i>Just give me a call
when you can</i>

1227
01:22:00.373 --> 01:22:02.584
<i>'cause I'm getting
a bit worried here.</i>

1228
01:22:02.585 --> 01:22:04.752
<i>♪ Oh. I'm on fire... ♪</i>

1229
01:22:04.753 --> 01:22:05.671
<i>Okay. amigo.</i>

1230
01:22:06.672 --> 01:22:10.968
<i>♪ Oh. oh. oh. I'm on fire ♪</i>

1231
01:22:12.219 --> 01:22:16.932
<i>♪ Oh. oh. I'm on fire ♪</i>

1232
01:22:39.788 --> 01:22:42.164
That's it. Jon.

1233
01:22:42.165 --> 01:22:44.501
That's everything I wanted.
That's it.

1234
01:22:44.502 --> 01:22:45.835
We got it.

1235
01:22:45.836 --> 01:22:48.463
The echo. Every imperfection.

1236
01:22:49.172 --> 01:22:50.673
The emotional atmosphere.

1237
01:22:50.674 --> 01:22:52.926
It's the cassette.
ready for vinyl.

1238
01:22:53.677 --> 01:22:55.928
And it's the story
you wanted to tell.

1239
01:22:55.929 --> 01:22:57.764
Okay. we just...
we can't let them

1240
01:22:57.765 --> 01:22:59.557
make it something
that it's not.

1241
01:22:59.558 --> 01:23:00.600
Right?

1242
01:23:00.601 --> 01:23:03.770
No singles. no tours.
no press. All right?

1243
01:23:03.771 --> 01:23:06.899
We have to let this album
breathe on its own.

1244
01:23:10.861 --> 01:23:15.991
This will be your first record
without a tour to support it.

1245
01:23:17.743 --> 01:23:20.161
- So not even any press?
- No.

1246
01:23:20.162 --> 01:23:21.203
We might need
to give the label

1247
01:23:21.204 --> 01:23:22.163
something to work with.

1248
01:23:22.164 --> 01:23:23.623
No. no. Jon.
I don't even want to be

1249
01:23:23.624 --> 01:23:24.624
on the cover. okay?

1250
01:23:24.625 --> 01:23:26.125
I don't wanna
have to explain it.

1251
01:23:26.126 --> 01:23:27.502
I don't even know if I can.

1252
01:23:28.170 --> 01:23:29.379
All right?

1253
01:23:31.173 --> 01:23:32.382
Thank you.

1254
01:23:34.051 --> 01:23:36.178
There's just one more track
I have to lay down.

1255
01:23:39.222 --> 01:23:43.101
<i>♪ Last night I dreamed that ♪</i>

1256
01:23:44.102 --> 01:23:47.022
<i>♪ I was a child ♪</i>

1257
01:23:48.941 --> 01:23:52.945
<i>♪ Out where the pines grow ♪</i>

1258
01:23:53.737 --> 01:23:56.782
<i>♪ Wild and tall ♪</i>

1259
01:23:58.742 --> 01:24:03.162
<i>♪ I was trying to ♪</i>

1260
01:24:03.163 --> 01:24:06.875
<i>♪ Make it home
Through the forest ♪</i>

1261
01:24:08.711 --> 01:24:15.718
<i>♪ Before the darkness falls ♪</i>

1262
01:24:18.136 --> 01:24:22.557
<i>♪ I heard the wind rustling ♪</i>

1263
01:24:23.475 --> 01:24:26.770
<i>♪ Through the trees ♪</i>

1264
01:24:28.480 --> 01:24:32.400
<i>♪ And ghostly voices ♪</i>

1265
01:24:33.611 --> 01:24:37.030
<i>♪ Rose from the fields ♪</i>

1266
01:24:38.073 --> 01:24:42.660
<i>♪ I ran
With my heart pounding ♪</i>

1267
01:24:42.661 --> 01:24:45.956
<i>♪ Down that broken path ♪</i>

1268
01:24:48.876 --> 01:24:52.629
<i>♪ With the devil ♪</i>

1269
01:24:52.630 --> 01:24:56.842
<i>♪ Snappin' at my heels ♪</i>

1270
01:24:58.135 --> 01:25:00.970
<i>♪ I broke through the trees ♪</i>

1271
01:25:00.971 --> 01:25:06.601
<i>♪ And there in the night ♪</i>

1272
01:25:08.061 --> 01:25:12.398
<i>♪ My father's house stood ♪</i>

1273
01:25:12.399 --> 01:25:16.654
<i>♪ Shining hard and bright ♪</i>

1274
01:25:17.780 --> 01:25:21.866
<i>♪ The branches and brambles ♪</i>

1275
01:25:21.867 --> 01:25:26.288
<i>♪ Tore my clothes
And scratched my arms ♪</i>

1276
01:25:27.665 --> 01:25:31.084
<i>♪ But I ran till I fell ♪</i>

1277
01:25:31.752 --> 01:25:36.339
<i>♪ Shaking in his arms ♪</i>

1278
01:25:47.350 --> 01:25:50.395
<i>♪ I awoke and I imagined ♪</i>

1279
01:25:50.896 --> 01:25:54.732
<i>♪ The hard things
That pulled us apart... ♪</i>

1280
01:25:54.733 --> 01:25:55.901
What do you want?

1281
01:25:57.610 --> 01:26:00.822
<i>♪ Will never again. sir... ♪</i>

1282
01:26:00.823 --> 01:26:01.989
Just to hear your voice.

1283
01:26:01.990 --> 01:26:06.286
<i>♪ Tear us
From each other's hearts ♪</i>

1284
01:26:08.205 --> 01:26:12.625
<i>♪ I got dressed
And to that house ♪</i>

1285
01:26:13.210 --> 01:26:15.420
<i>♪ I did ride ♪</i>

1286
01:26:17.672 --> 01:26:20.257
<i>♪ From out on the road ♪</i>

1287
01:26:20.258 --> 01:26:25.222
<i>♪ I could see
Its windows shining in light ♪</i>

1288
01:26:28.516 --> 01:26:29.475
<i>♪ I walked up... ♪</i>

1289
01:26:29.476 --> 01:26:31.854
So it's like this
the whole way through?

1290
01:26:33.230 --> 01:26:34.646
Yeah. And this is what

1291
01:26:34.647 --> 01:26:36.774
the final master's
gonna sound like?

1292
01:26:36.775 --> 01:26:38.150
Yeah.

1293
01:26:38.151 --> 01:26:39.236
Okay.

1294
01:26:40.695 --> 01:26:42.405
Stop it. Let's...

1295
01:26:42.990 --> 01:26:45.617
Pause it. Just stop for...
Can we stop it?

1296
01:26:46.159 --> 01:26:47.994
'Cause I've heard...
We've heard...

1297
01:26:47.995 --> 01:26:51.999
<i>♪ I told her my story... ♪</i>

1298
01:26:56.669 --> 01:27:00.715
You recognize this is a
highly unorthodox career move.

1299
01:27:01.258 --> 01:27:02.383
Right. Jon?

1300
01:27:02.384 --> 01:27:03.968
I mean.
I gotta be honest with you.

1301
01:27:03.969 --> 01:27:05.220
I don't understand this.

1302
01:27:06.013 --> 01:27:07.221
I don't understand why

1303
01:27:07.222 --> 01:27:08.597
an artist
would make this record.

1304
01:27:08.598 --> 01:27:10.099
It's a departure. Al.

1305
01:27:10.100 --> 01:27:11.184
Yeah. departure.

1306
01:27:11.684 --> 01:27:13.895
I'm surprised
Bruce even played it for you

1307
01:27:13.896 --> 01:27:16.148
because it sounds
like an accident.

1308
01:27:16.815 --> 01:27:18.565
You know.
it sounds unfinished.

1309
01:27:18.566 --> 01:27:19.651
That's the point.

1310
01:27:20.610 --> 01:27:22.278
I mean.
I'll spare you the details of

1311
01:27:22.279 --> 01:27:24.406
how far we went
to preserve that sound.

1312
01:27:25.783 --> 01:27:26.908
Well.

1313
01:27:26.909 --> 01:27:27.742
it's bold.

1314
01:27:28.576 --> 01:27:29.869
And I appreciate it.

1315
01:27:29.870 --> 01:27:32.121
It's just not for me.
and it...

1316
01:27:32.122 --> 01:27:35.417
I don't... Actually.
I don't know who it's for.

1317
01:27:36.001 --> 01:27:38.085
What I'd like to say is.
"Hey. take this back.

1318
01:27:38.086 --> 01:27:39.628
Bring me another record.

1319
01:27:39.629 --> 01:27:40.880
one with some... some...

1320
01:27:40.881 --> 01:27:44.091
some goddamn hits on it."
Right?

1321
01:27:44.092 --> 01:27:45.509
But...

1322
01:27:45.510 --> 01:27:46.844
you know. I know you guys.
and I know

1323
01:27:46.845 --> 01:27:48.512
that's not gonna happen. So...

1324
01:27:48.513 --> 01:27:50.473
- That's not gonna happen.
- Mm-hmm.

1325
01:27:51.183 --> 01:27:52.641
Here's the thing.

1326
01:27:52.642 --> 01:27:54.060
We're grateful to have

1327
01:27:54.061 --> 01:27:55.727
any new Bruce Springsteen
record. Right?

1328
01:27:55.728 --> 01:27:59.024
Because nobody but Bruce
can tell stories like these.

1329
01:28:00.275 --> 01:28:02.109
But radio can't play this.

1330
01:28:02.110 --> 01:28:03.821
- I understand.
- I mean. how are they gonna...

1331
01:28:04.446 --> 01:28:05.779
You know.

1332
01:28:05.780 --> 01:28:08.282
Are there radio edits
of these songs?

1333
01:28:08.283 --> 01:28:09.617
No. this is it.

1334
01:28:11.619 --> 01:28:12.912
Okay.

1335
01:28:12.913 --> 01:28:15.039
We will handle this
the best we can.

1336
01:28:15.040 --> 01:28:16.833
we'll do
everything we can to...

1337
01:28:16.834 --> 01:28:19.669
to protect it and release it

1338
01:28:20.170 --> 01:28:21.795
and... and give it
all it deserves.

1339
01:28:21.796 --> 01:28:24.091
That's great.
And we thank you. Al.

1340
01:28:25.008 --> 01:28:26.009
But...

1341
01:28:26.551 --> 01:28:27.802
you should know.

1342
01:28:29.179 --> 01:28:32.933
No singles. no tour. no press.

1343
01:28:37.104 --> 01:28:38.981
- No. really?
- No joke.

1344
01:28:39.564 --> 01:28:42.108
He's not even putting his face
on the album cover.

1345
01:28:42.109 --> 01:28:43.110
What?

1346
01:28:43.902 --> 01:28:45.528
- Nothing.
- You're being serious?

1347
01:28:48.198 --> 01:28:50.367
This is not gonna be good
for either one of us.

1348
01:28:50.868 --> 01:28:52.953
I'm not asking
for your understanding.

1349
01:28:53.661 --> 01:28:56.080
And I'm not here to explain
Bruce's thinking

1350
01:28:56.081 --> 01:28:58.541
or justify
his artistic choices.

1351
01:28:59.834 --> 01:29:03.170
I am here to make sure
the album is released

1352
01:29:03.171 --> 01:29:05.632
precisely the way he wants.

1353
01:29:06.716 --> 01:29:07.925
- That's it.
- Yeah.

1354
01:29:07.926 --> 01:29:09.093
Okay.

1355
01:29:09.094 --> 01:29:11.679
Whether or not you believe
in this particular album.

1356
01:29:13.056 --> 01:29:14.516
in this office.

1357
01:29:15.350 --> 01:29:16.601
my office.

1358
01:29:17.394 --> 01:29:19.354
we believe
in Bruce Springsteen.

1359
01:29:26.861 --> 01:29:27.945
...yet another dinner.

1360
01:29:27.946 --> 01:29:30.114
There's a club.
there's the sandwich.

1361
01:29:30.115 --> 01:29:32.200
That was it. right?
Okay. Enjoy.

1362
01:29:33.911 --> 01:29:35.245
All right.

1363
01:29:36.829 --> 01:29:37.914
You ready to order?

1364
01:29:37.915 --> 01:29:39.123
Uh. yeah. I think so.

1365
01:29:39.124 --> 01:29:40.332
You don't have a menu.

1366
01:29:40.333 --> 01:29:41.500
But I think I know
what you want.

1367
01:29:41.501 --> 01:29:42.668
It's the usual. right?

1368
01:29:42.669 --> 01:29:45.171
The omelet with the toast.
and a coffee.

1369
01:29:45.172 --> 01:29:46.463
I'm sorry
I didn't get you your menu.

1370
01:29:46.464 --> 01:29:47.715
Oh. that's fine. Faye.

1371
01:29:50.677 --> 01:29:51.761
Why are you doing this?

1372
01:29:54.847 --> 01:29:56.349
I didn't know how to face you.

1373
01:29:58.143 --> 01:30:00.103
It's not about facing me.

1374
01:30:02.605 --> 01:30:05.608
Look. we both knew
that this was casual at first.

1375
01:30:09.737 --> 01:30:13.075
But things changed.
I thought maybe we changed.

1376
01:30:15.953 --> 01:30:17.245
I know you did.

1377
01:30:21.416 --> 01:30:23.750
I don't know
how to love you any better

1378
01:30:23.751 --> 01:30:25.378
or any more
than the way I do now.

1379
01:30:28.715 --> 01:30:30.425
And I know that's not enough.

1380
01:30:36.223 --> 01:30:37.724
I'm lost here.

1381
01:30:39.017 --> 01:30:40.643
I'm buried here.

1382
01:30:43.730 --> 01:30:45.983
That's why
I'm headed to California.

1383
01:30:48.068 --> 01:30:49.443
What?

1384
01:30:49.444 --> 01:30:51.029
I bought a house in L.A.

1385
01:30:53.948 --> 01:30:56.368
You know. it's the first thing
I've ever had that's mine.

1386
01:30:58.245 --> 01:31:00.080
that I own. and...

1387
01:31:04.459 --> 01:31:06.336
I need to go out there
on my own.

1388
01:31:13.635 --> 01:31:14.968
You're moving to Los Angeles

1389
01:31:14.969 --> 01:31:16.970
and you wait
until now to tell me?

1390
01:31:16.971 --> 01:31:18.390
Well. I didn't know.

1391
01:31:21.684 --> 01:31:23.310
I was trying
to find the right time.

1392
01:31:23.311 --> 01:31:24.978
but there's never been
a right time.

1393
01:31:24.979 --> 01:31:26.898
You think
this is about timing?

1394
01:31:29.192 --> 01:31:30.776
This isn't
about California. Bruce.

1395
01:31:30.777 --> 01:31:31.860
This is about you running away

1396
01:31:31.861 --> 01:31:33.362
from everything
that scares you.

1397
01:31:33.363 --> 01:31:35.657
From us.
From what we could be.

1398
01:31:36.949 --> 01:31:39.243
And don't give me that
"it's not you. it's me" crap.

1399
01:31:39.244 --> 01:31:41.287
I know you're scared.

1400
01:31:41.288 --> 01:31:43.372
I've seen it every time
you look at Haley.

1401
01:31:43.373 --> 01:31:44.498
Every time you look at me.

1402
01:31:44.499 --> 01:31:45.832
you think
that you're protecting us

1403
01:31:45.833 --> 01:31:47.209
by pushing us away.
but you're just hiding--

1404
01:31:47.210 --> 01:31:49.003
I don't wanna hurt you. Faye.

1405
01:31:51.714 --> 01:31:53.175
I don't wanna hurt anyone.

1406
01:31:55.760 --> 01:31:57.429
I've done enough
of that already.

1407
01:31:58.430 --> 01:32:00.473
Then what about facing it?

1408
01:32:02.809 --> 01:32:05.602
What about actually
dealing with your shit.

1409
01:32:05.603 --> 01:32:07.522
instead of running from it?

1410
01:32:11.943 --> 01:32:14.027
You say that you can't love me
like I deserve

1411
01:32:14.028 --> 01:32:16.114
but the truth is.
you won't even try.

1412
01:32:16.906 --> 01:32:19.032
Because trying
means facing yourself.

1413
01:32:19.033 --> 01:32:21.035
and that terrifies you.

1414
01:32:23.955 --> 01:32:27.291
And Haley and I.
we are not here to play house.

1415
01:32:27.292 --> 01:32:30.419
- We are real people.
- Yeah. I know that.

1416
01:32:30.420 --> 01:32:31.503
I believed in you.

1417
01:32:31.504 --> 01:32:34.716
I believed that you could be
the man you pretend to be.

1418
01:32:40.472 --> 01:32:41.555
You know.
I think you're right.

1419
01:32:41.556 --> 01:32:42.931
I think you should go.

1420
01:32:42.932 --> 01:32:45.601
because until you can
be honest with yourself.

1421
01:32:45.602 --> 01:32:47.604
you're never gonna be
honest with me.

1422
01:32:49.772 --> 01:32:50.773
Faye.

1423
01:32:51.524 --> 01:32:53.193
I gotta get back to work.

1424
01:32:54.486 --> 01:32:56.778
I hope you find what you're
looking for in California.

1425
01:32:56.779 --> 01:32:57.780
I really do.

1426
01:32:59.574 --> 01:33:01.159
I really do.

1427
01:33:10.168 --> 01:33:11.002
You all right?

1428
01:33:36.153 --> 01:33:38.863
This thing runs
in my blood. Jon.

1429
01:33:40.657 --> 01:33:44.327
My pops. aunts. cousins.

1430
01:33:47.330 --> 01:33:48.623
Like poison.

1431
01:33:51.376 --> 01:33:53.920
You know
what Flannery O'Connor says.

1432
01:33:57.299 --> 01:33:59.801
"Where you come from is gone.

1433
01:34:01.428 --> 01:34:04.889
And where you thought you were
going to. was never there.

1434
01:34:06.808 --> 01:34:11.062
And nothing outside of you
can give you any place.

1435
01:34:13.315 --> 01:34:19.196
In yourself. right now.
is the only place you got."

1436
01:34:27.537 --> 01:34:29.414
Come on.
Let me buy you breakfast.

1437
01:34:29.914 --> 01:34:31.707
You look like
you could use some pancakes.

1438
01:34:31.708 --> 01:34:33.460
No. I'm good. Jon.

1439
01:34:35.253 --> 01:34:36.879
I'm just gonna hang here.

1440
01:34:43.428 --> 01:34:45.430
All right.
I got something for you.

1441
01:34:47.599 --> 01:34:48.600
Okay.

1442
01:34:59.736 --> 01:35:00.820
Let's just listen.

1443
01:35:02.447 --> 01:35:03.448
Okay.

1444
01:36:49.596 --> 01:36:50.597
Ready?

1445
01:37:35.642 --> 01:37:36.933
- More coffee? Okay.
- I'm okay.

1446
01:37:38.227 --> 01:37:40.605
So... Boise City and then...

1447
01:37:43.566 --> 01:37:45.276
Three days. maybe four.

1448
01:37:51.699 --> 01:37:53.284
I think she's right.

1449
01:37:56.203 --> 01:37:57.705
Goddamn it. she's right.

1450
01:38:33.658 --> 01:38:35.033
<i>Come on up and guess</i>

1451
01:38:35.034 --> 01:38:37.160
<i>the weight of the prize hog.</i>

1452
01:38:37.161 --> 01:38:39.205
<i>A dollar a guess.
Winner takes all.</i>

1453
01:38:44.961 --> 01:38:46.587
<i>A dollar a guess.</i>

1454
01:38:46.588 --> 01:38:48.255
<i>Winner takes all.
Winner takes all.</i>

1455
01:38:51.843 --> 01:38:53.302
<i>Come on. folks.</i>

1456
01:39:57.116 --> 01:39:58.284
You okay?

1457
01:40:02.705 --> 01:40:04.165
Bruce. you okay?

1458
01:40:08.210 --> 01:40:09.336
<i>Hey.</i>

1459
01:40:11.463 --> 01:40:12.757
What's going on?

1460
01:40:13.716 --> 01:40:15.134
Hey. hey. hey.

1461
01:40:17.511 --> 01:40:19.304
Look at me. look at me. yeah?

1462
01:40:19.305 --> 01:40:21.348
Just breathe. okay?
Nice and slow. yeah?

1463
01:40:22.224 --> 01:40:23.308
Okay. I'm here.

1464
01:40:24.644 --> 01:40:26.061
Yeah.

1465
01:40:26.062 --> 01:40:27.354
Let's get out of here.

1466
01:40:30.149 --> 01:40:31.859
I. uh... I don't know
what to do. Jon.

1467
01:40:32.735 --> 01:40:33.736
He's not right.

1468
01:40:34.361 --> 01:40:35.946
<i>It's that bad. huh?</i>

1469
01:40:35.947 --> 01:40:36.863
I don't know. man.

1470
01:40:36.864 --> 01:40:38.115
I've never seen him
like this before.

1471
01:40:39.116 --> 01:40:41.367
<i>Okay. you just get him to L.A.</i>

1472
01:40:41.368 --> 01:40:42.535
- All right.
<i>- Quick as you can.</i>

1473
01:40:42.536 --> 01:40:43.537
I'll keep you updated.

1474
01:40:58.469 --> 01:41:00.137
You want a sandwich
or something?

1475
01:41:03.182 --> 01:41:04.558
Nah. nah. we get outta here.

1476
01:41:05.727 --> 01:41:06.810
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

1477
01:41:06.811 --> 01:41:08.145
- All right. buddy.
- All right.

1478
